Bioluminescent algae at Jervis Bay, NSW 🇦🇺 Apply for a feature following the link in our bio and we will publish your photos in our account: @explorationfervor

They are a group of tiny marine organisms that can produce an ethereal glow in the dark. The algae's glow is actually a natural defense mechanism; the light flashes occur when the algae's environment is disturbed.

When the mass of dinoflagellates are mixed up by waves or larger ocean life, a chemical reaction involving enzyme luciferase and compound luciferin produced by the algae is what causes bioluminescence, the creation of light by a living organism.

📷 @Jordan_Robins

node.text:
Adrenaline rush above the clouds ⛅️
Who would you try this with?

Skydiving, is a method of transiting from a high point in the atmosphere to the surface of Earth with the aid of gravity, involving the control of speed during the descent using a parachute or parachutes.

For human skydiving, it may involve a phase of more or less free-falling (the skydiving segment) which is a period when the parachute has not yet been deployed and the body gradually accelerates to terminal velocity.

📽 @rein_skywalker
📍 @skydivemosselbay, Mossel Bay, South Africa
🎶 My Girl - The Temptations

node.text:
Norway views from Mt. Bispen ⛰ Apply for a feature following the link in our bio and we will publish your photos in our account: @explorationfervor 

The views of these Norwegian mountains from top of Bispen (The Bishop) rise steep above the famous Trollstigen road and Isterdalen valley. These mountains attracks climbers, hikers and basejumpers. The prime hiking season is July through September, and you don't have to be a mountain climber to reach the summits. However, a good portion of mountain experience will be useful.

Would you dare to hike this mountain? 👇

📽 @ellisivbrain
📍Mt Bispen, Trollstigen, Norway
